The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are as of the close of trading.  The  IGBC Index (IGBC)  rose 0.2 percent to 15,240.93, while the
 Colcap Index (COLCAP)  increased 0.2 percent to 1,802.34.  Ecopetrol SA (EC)  , Colombiaâ€™s largest  oil company ,
rose 0.9 percent to 5,650 pesos. The government will seek the
involvement of Chinese companies in a pipeline to transport oil
from the Caribbean to the Pacific coast, Mines and Energy
Minister Mauricio Cardenas said in an e-mailed statement.  Canacol Energy Ltd. (CNE)  , the Calgary-based oil
company that operates fields in Colombia, dropped 2.3 percent to
1,300 pesos. Crude for June delivery dropped to a three-month
low in  New York .  To contact the reporter on this story:
